<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Categories/Blog on Create A Van Life</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/categories/blog/</link><description>Recent content in Categories/Blog on Create A Van Life</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><copyright>© 2026 Create A Van Life</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/categories/blog/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Alternator Charging for Portable Power Stations</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/alternator-charging-for-power-stations/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/alternator-charging-for-power-stations/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Alternator charging is often the fastest way to stabilize portable power in real travel routines.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Why It Matters
 &lt;div id="why-it-matters" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#why-it-matters" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A modest battery with fast alternator recovery can outperform a larger battery with weak replenishment.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How Many Watt-Hours Do I Need in a Van?</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/how-many-watt-hours-do-i-need/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/how-many-watt-hours-do-i-need/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Sizing your system starts with daily behavior, not product marketing. Track real device use first, then choose capacity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Practical Sizing Method
 &lt;div id="practical-sizing-method" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#practical-sizing-method" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;List daily loads (laptop, router, lights, fan, charging).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Estimate hours used per load.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a conservative daily total and add margin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Match station size to both usage and recharge reality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Diagram placeholder: Daily load worksheet and margin model.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Portable Power vs Full Electrical Build</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/portable-power-vs-full-electrical-build/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/portable-power-vs-full-electrical-build/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This decision should follow your use pattern, not online hype. Portable systems reduce install risk; fixed systems improve integration and scaling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;When Portable Power Wins
 &lt;div id="when-portable-power-wins" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#when-portable-power-wins" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Portable power wins when your real life is moving faster than your build plan. When you are tired, behind, and still need tomorrow to work, a portable setup can keep your routine stable without adding install complexity.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Solar Input Explained for Portable Power Stations</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/solar-input-explained-for-power-stations/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/solar-input-explained-for-power-stations/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Solar input is useful, but it is only reliable when panel sizing, weather assumptions, and charge windows are realistic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Core Concepts
 &lt;div id="core-concepts" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#core-concepts" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Input limits, panel voltage/current matching, and harvest variability drive outcomes more than headline panel wattage.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Budget Kitchen Setup for Van Life</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/budget-kitchen-setup-for-van-life/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/budget-kitchen-setup-for-van-life/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A practical kitchen cuts food costs and keeps road life sustainable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Core Setup
 &lt;div id="core-setup" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#core-setup" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two-burner stove&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;One pan + one pot + prep knife&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dry pantry bins and simple cleanup flow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;What to Skip at First
 &lt;div id="what-to-skip-at-first" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#what-to-skip-at-first" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Large permanent installs without real usage data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Single-purpose gadgets that consume storage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Read next:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Budget Van Electrical: Simple vs DIY</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/budget-van-electrical-simple-vs-diy/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/budget-van-electrical-simple-vs-diy/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The right electrical strategy depends on your actual usage, not social media build standards.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Simple System (Power Station)
 &lt;div id="simple-system-power-station" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#simple-system-power-station" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Best if you want fast setup, low risk, and minimal wiring. Cost is predictable and troubleshooting is easier.
We’re keeping this high-level—no wiring instructions here. For installs, follow manufacturer guidance or work with a qualified installer.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How Much Solar Do You Need in a Van?</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/how-much-solar-do-you-need-in-a-van/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/how-much-solar-do-you-need-in-a-van/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Most people should estimate usage first, then choose solar. Start with a daily load list in watt-hours.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Quick Sizing Rule
 &lt;div id="quick-sizing-rule" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#quick-sizing-rule" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Light use: 200W&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Moderate daily use: 300W-400W&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Heavy remote work + fridge: 500W+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then match battery capacity to at least one day of use.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How to Start Van Life on a Budget</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/how-to-start-van-life-on-a-budget/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/how-to-start-van-life-on-a-budget/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Starting van life on a budget is mostly about sequencing. People overspend when they buy comfort upgrades before core systems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Phase 1: Buy the Right Van
 &lt;div id="phase-1-buy-the-right-van" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#phase-1-buy-the-right-van" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A reliable used van with service history beats a newer van you cannot afford to maintain. Budget for an inspection and first-month repairs.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Portable Power Stations vs Full Electrical Build</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/portable-power-stations-vs-full-electrical-build/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/portable-power-stations-vs-full-electrical-build/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This decision controls budget, build timeline, and failure risk.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Power Station Wins If
 &lt;div id="power-station-wins-if" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#power-station-wins-if" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You need power quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your loads are moderate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You prefer lower install risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;DIY System Wins If
 &lt;div id="diy-system-wins-if" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#diy-system-wins-if" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You run high-watt appliances daily.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You want deep integration and maximum control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can design safe electrical systems or hire help.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Practical Recommendation
 &lt;div id="practical-recommendation" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#practical-recommendation" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start with a quality station, then move to fixed electrical when your daily usage data proves you need it.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Tools You’ll Actually Use in a First Build</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/tools-youll-actually-use-in-a-first-build/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/tools-youll-actually-use-in-a-first-build/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The fastest way to overspend on a build is buying every tool recommended online.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Buy First
 &lt;div id="buy-first" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#buy-first" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drill/driver combo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jigsaw + quality blades&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Crimper + multimeter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PPE and measuring tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Borrow or Rent
 &lt;div id="borrow-or-rent" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#borrow-or-rent" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialty saws&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rare-use heavy tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Why This Matters
 &lt;div id="why-this-matters" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#why-this-matters" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tool quality affects safety and finish quality, but tool count does not.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Van Internet: What Actually Works Off-Grid</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/van-internet-what-actually-works-off-grid/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/van-internet-what-actually-works-off-grid/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Reliable van internet comes from layered redundancy, not one magic device.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Baseline Setup
 &lt;div id="baseline-setup" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#baseline-setup" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Primary hotspot with external antenna support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Secondary carrier or tether backup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mounting and cable routing that protects signal quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Common Mistakes
 &lt;div id="common-mistakes" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#common-mistakes" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Chasing theoretical max speeds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using only one network&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ignoring power draw of network hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Read next:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Ventilation Mistakes New Van Lifers Make</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/ventilation-mistakes-new-van-lifers-make/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/ventilation-mistakes-new-van-lifers-make/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Bad airflow causes more daily frustration than most first-time builders expect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Mistake 1: No Crossflow Plan
 &lt;div id="mistake-1-no-crossflow-plan" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#mistake-1-no-crossflow-plan" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A roof fan alone is not enough. Pair extraction with side-window intake.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>